Recently we have witnessed the success of models like GPT-4 [openai2023gpt4] in a multitude of NLP applications that involve multiple modalities and domain specific adaptations.
While LLMs are often treated as generative models, they can be easily adopted in search and reasoning tasks in many tools and pipelines \footnote{E.g., \url{https://haystack.deepset.ai/}}.
Nonetheless, as seen in the past all these specialized domains can better benefit from the inclusion of symbolic knowledge in machine methods [Alshahrani:NuroSym17].
Here we focus on two distinct applications: (1) semantic image and video search and (2) technical document understanding.